<pre>
CHMOD
-who letters:
u user (me)
g group (all)
o others (not u or g)
a every single person

-permission letters:
r read
w write
x execute
X execute only if file is in a directory
s set user or group ID

-operations:
+ add
- take away
= set exactly and remove all others

>chmod a+r foo.txt
grants read permissions to everyone for foo.txt
</pre>
